to go play junior hockey down

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:09.944
in Portland, Oregon, I was still
playing all those other sports,

00:03:09.944 --> 00:03:11.610
and to this day still
play other sports.

00:03:11.610 --> 00:03:14.640
So the NHL to me was always
like this lottery ticket.

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:17.280
You know, you work really hard,
you do everything you can,

00:03:17.280 --> 00:03:19.780
but even at that there's so
much that's out of your control.

00:03:19.780 --> 00:03:22.624
So it was kind of
a dream, but not

00:03:22.624 --> 00:03:23.790
one that I really relied on.

00:03:23.790 --> 00:03:26.730
So probably about
like 17 years old,

00:03:26.730 --> 00:03:29.430
I started playing against
other people, guys

00:03:29.430 --> 00:03:31.984
that were older than me that
eventually started making it.

00:03:31.984 --> 00:03:33.900
And when I saw those
guys make it, I was like,

00:03:33.900 --> 00:03:36.390
I can play against those
guys, so maybe there's

00:03:36.390 --> 00:03:37.320
a chance, right?

00:03:37.320 --> 00:03:41.280
But you know, I was probably
three years into my NHL career

00:03:41.280 --> 00:03:44.525
before I felt like, oh,
actually I belong here.

00:03:44.525 --> 00:03:45.630
Like, it felt real.

00:03:45.630 --> 00:03:47.880
SPEAKER 1: So talk a little
bit about your NHL career.

00:03:47.880 --> 00:03:49.305
What was the highlight?

00:03:49.305 --> 00:03:50.930
